Fig. 36I ‒J
). Abdomen as in male ( Fig. 36G‒H ). Total length 12.4; carapace 5.44 long, 3.6 wide. Carapace with the cephalic region elevated ( Figs 1B , 36G ). Legs: robust and densely coated with setae, mainly on the ventral region of pairs I‒III; legs I‒II with ventro-prolateral and ventro-retrolateral tibial macrosetae of similar size, and metatarsal macrosetae of different sizes ( Fig. 7A‒C ,
36I ‒J
